The early church understood the power of these words. They lived by them, suffered for them, and saw God move mightily through their faithful obedience. We are called to the same standard of faith.', '["Father, help me to truly understand and live out the truth of James 2:8","Lord, let the reality of loving your neighbor transform my daily walk with You","Holy Spirit, open my eyes to see the depth of wisdom in this passage from James","God, remove every hindrance that prevents me from fully embracing this truth","Lord, let Your Word concerning loving your neighbor produce lasting fruit in my life"]'::jsonb, '["I declare that loving your neighbor is my reality in Christ Jesus","I walk in the truth of James 2:8 every day of my life","By faith, I receive every blessing that God has prepared for me","I am established in the Word of God and nothing shall move me","The power of God works mightily in me and through me","\"Prayer is not asking. It is a longing of the soul.\" — Mahatma Gandhi","\"Grace means that all of your mistakes now serve a purpose instead of serving shame.\" — Brene Brown","\"You can never learn that Christ is all you need, until Christ is all you have.\" — Corrie ten Boom","I prophesy over my life: the word of God concerning loving your neighbor is established and cannot be reversed","I decree and declare that every plan of the enemy against my destiny is destroyed by the power of God''s Word"]'::jsonb, 'Moses Afolabi'),
(366, '2027-01-03', 'Speak and Act by the Law of Liberty', '{"reference":"James 2:12","text":"So speak ye, and so do, as they that shall be judged by the law of liberty."}'::jsonb, 'The words of James 2:12 carry a powerful message for believers today. So speak ye, and so do, as they that shall be judged by the law of liberty. This truth is not merely historical; it is a living reality that shapes our daily walk with God.

