(368, '2027-01-05', 'The Power of the Tongue', '{"reference":"James 3:5-6","text":"Even so the tongue is a little member, and boasteth great things. Behold, how great a matter a little fire kindleth! And the tongue is a fire, a world of iniquity."}'::jsonb, 'The words of James 3:5-6 carry a powerful message for believers today. Even so the tongue is a little member, and boasteth great things. Behold, how great a matter a little fire kindleth! And the tongue is a fire, a world of iniquity. This truth is not merely historical; it is a living reality that shapes our daily walk with God.

When we meditate on this passage, we discover layers of meaning that speak directly to our circumstances. The controlling speech revealed here is foundational to our Christian faith and practice.

